snippet.textDisplay: Well, well, well! Let me see now! The L.A. Lakers were blown out by Beantown's Celtics, and again by the City of Brotherly Love's Seventy-sixers despite LeBron Raymone James, Sr. surpassing Kobe Bean Bryant's all-time scoring record. However, records are made to be broken, to say the least. During their extremely long flight back to LAX, the L.A. Lakers' reserved bench will still have to straighten up and fly right, now they're experiencing their loss in double digits, fate is still hanging around. The Clippers will await their meeting on January 28th. That's the way the mop flops, I guess! Such is life. Ciao!
